data.name: pHisPred
data.description: A bioinformatic tool for identifying protein histidine phosphorylation sites

evidence: "pHisPred is developed by Jian Zhao (zhao_doctor@hotmail.com). For questions and comments, please contact Jian or submit an issue on github."

"A bioinformatic tool for identifying protein histidine phosphorylation sites" and usage via command line: "python pHisPred.py -f input.fa -o output -t euka" indicate it is an end-user analysis tool, not a library.

Installation and usage sections only describe running Python scripts from the repository (e.g., "python pHisPred.py ...", "python train_model.py ...") with no mention of package managers, releases, or containers, implying distribution via source repo.
